{"questionId":"9066282","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">This question is about the decomposition of hydrogen peroxide.</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">Hydrogen peroxide decomposes to water and oxygen when a catalyst such as potassium iodide, KI, is added.</span></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><br>2H<sub>2</sub>O<sub>2</sub> (aq)&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\xrightarrow{{{\\text{KI (aq)}}}}\">\n  <mover>\n    <mo>→</mo>\n    <mpadded width=\"+0.611em\" lspace=\"0.278em\" voffset=\".15em\">\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <mtext>KI (aq)</mtext>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n    </mpadded>\n  </mover>\n</math></span> O<sub>2</sub> (g) + 2H<sub>2</sub>O (l)</span></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">MnO<sub>2</sub> is another possible catalyst for the reaction. State the IUPAC name for MnO<sub>2</sub>.</span></p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">manganese(IV) oxide</span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><em><strong>OR</strong></em></span></p>\n<p><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\">manganese dioxide &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong>[✔]</strong></span></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><span style=\"background-color:#ffffff;\"><strong>Note:&nbsp;</strong>Accept “manganese(IV) dioxide”.</span></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9066282","referenceCode":"19M.2.hl.TZ1.4b(v)","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"MnO2 is another possible catalyst for the reaction. State the IUPAC name for MnO2.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"b(v)","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 9: Redox processes","9.1 Oxidation and reduction","Core","Topic 9: Redox processes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}